==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hubble Space Telescope
<hw>Hub"ble Space
Tel"e*scope</hw></mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A large
astronomical optical telescope placed into orbit around the earth, from
which, in the absence of absorption and distortion by the earth's
atmosphere, clear high-resolution images of astronomical objects can be
obtained in the visible, infrared, and ultraviolet wavelengths. The
telescope was launched into orbit on April 24, 1990. Since then the
telescope has taken thousands of images, many of them unique, recording
never before seen astronomical phenomena. Service missions were
performed in 1993 and 1997, during which astronauts upgraded or replaced
equipment on the telescope.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

